ZH: 来到一个新的国家，我们要入乡随俗。
EN: When in a new country, we should follow local customs.

ZH: 作为一个客人，我们应该入乡随俗。
EN: As a guest, we should follow local customs.

ZH: 在这个小镇上，入乡随俗是很重要的。
EN: In this small town, it is important to follow local customs.

ZH: 他一直遵循着入乡随俗的原则。
EN: He has always followed the principle of when in Rome, do as the Romans do.

ZH: 学会入乡随俗将会更容易融入当地社会。
EN: Learning to adapt to local customs will make it easier to integrate into the local community.

ZH: 没有人愿意和一个不懂入乡随俗的人交朋友。
EN: No one wants to be friends with someone who doesn't follow local customs.

ZH: 入乡随俗是交流和理解文化差异的重要方式。
EN: Following local customs is an important way to communicate and understand cultural differences.

ZH: 在庆祝他们的节日时，我们应该入乡随俗。
EN: When celebrating their holidays, we should follow local customs.

ZH: 出国留学的学生都需要学会入乡随俗。
EN: Students studying abroad all need to learn to adapt to local customs.

ZH: 作为一名外教，遵守当地的习俗是很重要的。
EN: As a foreign teacher, it is important to adhere to local customs.

ZH: 参加当地的传统庆典会更好地帮助我们入乡随俗。
EN: Attending local traditional celebrations will better help us adapt to local customs.

ZH: 入乡随俗是一个基本的尊重他人的表现。
EN: Following local customs is a basic form of respect for others.

ZH: 在这个国家，我们需要入乡随俗生活。
EN: In this country, we need to adapt to local customs.

ZH: 他的确是一个很懂入乡随俗的人。
EN: He is indeed someone who understands and follows local customs.

ZH: 只有当我们入乡随俗，我们才能更好地了解这个国家。
EN: Only by adapting to local customs can we better understand this country.

ZH: 遵守当地规矩是入乡随俗的重要内容之一。
EN: Following local customs is one of the important aspects of adapting to a new place.

ZH: 参加当地的传统活动是入乡随俗的好机会。
EN: Participating in local traditional activities is a good opportunity to adapt to local customs.

ZH: 如果我们不入乡随俗，可能会给自己带来很多不便。
EN: If we do not adapt to local customs, it may bring us a lot of inconvenience.

ZH: 尊重他人的宗教信仰是入乡随俗的一部分。
EN: Respecting the religious beliefs of others is part of adapting to local customs.

ZH: 在这里，我们需要学会入乡随俗才能更好地融入社会。
EN: Here, we need to learn to adapt to local customs in order to better integrate into society.
